    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "``` python\np.ix[:,datetime.datetime(2012, 1, 1):datetime.datetime(2012,2,1)]\np.ix[:, 0:1]\n```\n\nThe first one will return shape 4,2,2 because indexing by label is inclusive. The second one will return shape 4,1,2 because indexing by loc will follow normal slice behavior. \n\nThe problem is that the minor axis in your example is an IntIndex. So it tries to match by label first, which works so it's inclusive. \n"
