    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "That makes sense - I assumed the date ranges were the minor & minor axis but obviously the first one was getting assigned to items.\n\nI can see that having an inclusive end point makes sense for a slice of an unordered index, but it's a bit surprising for a date index and is different to what I'm used to from `scikits.timeseries`. I guess that ship has sailed however and there's no chance that DatetimeIndexes will be treated specially so as to not include the endpoint.\n\nI don't think there's an actual bug here - just my incorrect understanding/intuition so I'll close the issue.\n"
